content.detailedDescription:
18 years ago my sister had picked me up in the middle of the night , we headed toward our grandmothers home that was an hour drive . driving down the road , talking , listening to music, nothing in sight , until we looked over as we turned the curve in the road. that's when we both laid eyes on it. it had to have been 100ft away "close" we couldn't keep our eyes off of it . as soon as my sister went to make eye contact with me it disappeared. i saw what "was" not from this world. lights, no sound,and fast as lightening. i am one who was brought up in church , never did i ever believe or imagine there was anything out of this world coming to our world. i am human though and i do understand that people are skeptical. i have lived all these years knowing what we had seen. we talked about the sighting but not a whole lot anymore. but i know it was real , very real. and seeing is believing. i just don't understand why there are so many people in the world today that have seen with there own eyes, why are there so many disbelieve ? so many witnesses. but yet we don't stand united and demand answers? i know now myself and my sister are not the only ones who have seen the truth of life beyond earth. and i'm glad i get to share with people who may be skeptical. i know you don't know me , if your reading this your already in question. the truth is behind the eyes of us people who have seen . my sister had asked me a question one day " id just like to share" she asked: wonder why we got to see it and not everyone in this world did? why does it seem like it is selective? or is it? these questions made me think. i guess there is questioning. but who knows whats to come i guess. all i know is that rather anyone believes me or not i got to share my thoughts and our story . you'll just have to believe or fight for the truth from the government.
thank you for reading , and i hope our story has helped some.
content.summary: Was 18 years ago. i was affraid of reporting to police. my sister & i had been on our way back from chilicothe to hillsboro rocky fork lake. in the middle of the night the object was right next to us in a field floating just above ground we stoped

content.detailedDescription: Watching 5:30 news, wife calls from store 3 miles away, asks me to go outside look to north, can i see anything? went outside,observed bright glowing object nne at about 80 degrees above horizon,absolutely stationary. thought it may be a drone holding position for surveillance. after i got the 10 power binocs. i could see now a jellyfish shape completely stationary and not changing shape, but approx. asprin sized as viewed thru the binocs. by now she gets home and we both trade off looking thru binocs. she calls channel news, about 45 miles nne is the direction and distance of their station and they are aware of it and had gotten numerous calls about it already but do not know what it is. if they could tell the angle and direction above horiz.As seen from their position we may be able to determine its altitude and size. it appeared to be glowing white, possibly from setting sun reflecting off its surface. it disappeared from sight after dusk.It could have been a huge clear balloon but balloons generally do not hold position for an hour and a half unless tethered,and if was viewed from 45 miles distant would be an extremely long tether indeed endangering passing commercial aircraft.(there were 2 commercial aircraft observed heading west during the time of this sighting and approx. position.)our neighbor next door saw the object as well, he was viewing it from his driveway 30 feet east of us.
content.summary: Veiwed w/binocs asprin sized jellyfish 1.5 hrs. statioary

content.detailedDescription: Me and my girlfriend were leaving the bank heading westbound on rockton rd. saw 3-5 red/orange lights in southern sky 3 in a perfect triangle formation, 1-2 in a straight line in parallel positioning. we thought it was maybe helicopter search party at first. was about to make a northbound turn onto dorr rd and saw another 2-3 lights lower in between rooflines. as i turned north she was describing them to me as they were too my south, i turned right immediately into a neighborhood to get turned around to witness event. as i got turned back facing southbound there appeared to be upwards of 9 orbs, hovering, moving slowly in tree line/roofline, at one point two sets of three were in perfect triangle formation, at another time they were in a straight line. i drove down to kelly meyers park in roscoe, il and pulled over to get out, at this point all the hair on my body was sticking straight up in disbelief at what i was seeing. we pulled over next to a small suv that appeared to be witnessing the same event but as i went to get out of ,y car they left. the lights started moving in different directions, a few went vertical and just seemed to turn off. a few went east and turned off. two were heading northwest so i pulled out to go follow. as we were driving down the road we stopped for a stop light and tried to look back up and they were just gone. the lights were mainly a fiery orange color, but at time seemed more yellow and others almost apple red. no flashing or real pulsing. we saw several planes fly over head during the process, i can not explain what i just witnessed. by time the last two lights disappeared i noted the clock at 7:11 pm local time. whole event lasted maybe 5-6 minutes. too long for planes passing by, and i know it wasn’t a plane as we watch them fly overhead all the time.

i then got out my phone and started filming. i took two series of videos each about four minutes long. the first video looks at the object from more of a wide angle. the second zooms in very close to the object and it actually took my breath away when i saw it's shape and the light that was coming from it.

i live in the third most populous county in the entire country and our air space is insanely busy. there is a very active air force base here, a very busy air port four miles away, and they build bell helicopters, and apache helicopters just a few miles from my house. additionally, there is a hospital within a couple miles of my house with a super busy medivac helicopter and lastly the national guard is periodically flying their black hawks into the desert for practice. lastly, there is a gunner range for the "wart hogs" about 100 miles away.

i love planes and wish i would have been a helicopter pilot. hence i am always looking in the sky to see what is flying overhead and whatever this was it's not like anything i've ever seen before. 

i would love to know if someone has a logical explanation for what i saw.
